Definition: a new trial in which issues already litigated and to which the court has already rendered a verdict or decision are reexamined by the same court
Example: occurs when the initial trial is found to have been improper or unfair due to procedural errors
Synonyms: verb, social, retry, trial, noun, group, law, c, a, new, in, which, issues, already, litigated, and, to, the, court, has, rendered, verdict, or, decision, are, reexamined, by, same, occurs, when, initial, is, found, have, been, improper, unfair, due, procedural, errors
Category: noun.act
